 (0) Don't change any cmdFlag.

 (1) Disable PUSH/DERK: Don't use remote keys F(X).
     This mode uses only the local passphrase. The server can't
     restart without the local passphrase. 
     Can't use autodestruction certificate KCTL.

     This is the best way with correct use of sysop.txt and boot
     passphrase.

 (2) Enable PUSH/DERK: Enable remote keys F(X).
     This mude uses the remote F(X) keys. The server can be
     restarted. The control of F(X) is menaged by KCTL certificate.
     You can use the autodestruction certificate KCTL.
OptFlag hideboot	#c1
OptFlag hidesysop	#c1
OptFlag noderk 		#c2
OptFlag hideboot 	#c2
OptFlag hidesysop	#c2
